I'm a bit confused on this PR. I thought this was defining tables that would be programmed via gNMI by the SDN controller or network controller - so, the tables connected to those nodes in this graph: https://github.com/sonic-net/SONiC/blob/master/doc/smart-switch/high-availability/smart-switch-ha-detailed-design.md#11-upstream-config-programming-path

But, the tables defined don't match up. E.g. there is no DASH_ENI_TABLE definition, and there is a DASH_HA_SET_TABLE definition but it is programmed via hamgrd/zmq, not by anything using protobuf.

I think I am probably just confused about what this PR is. Jing or Riff, can you clarify?

> I'm a bit confused on this PR. I thought this was defining tables that would be programmed via gNMI by the SDN controller or network controller - so, the tables connected to those nodes in this graph: https://github.com/sonic-net/SONiC/blob/master/doc/smart-switch/high-availability/smart-switch-ha-detailed-design.md#11-upstream-config-programming-path
> 
> But, the tables defined don't match up. E.g. there is no DASH_ENI_TABLE definition, and there is a DASH_HA_SET_TABLE definition but it is programmed via hamgrd/zmq, not by anything using protobuf.
> 
> I think I am probably just confused about what this PR is. Jing or Riff, can you clarify?

Hi Oliver, this PR is to define the message protocol for 
1. tables used for hamgrd<->swss communication. 
1. tables used for SDN controller <-> hamgrd  communication. 

`DASH_ENI_TABLE` is added already [eni.proto](https://github.com/sonic-net/sonic-dash-api/blob/master/proto/eni.proto).

Swss-comm only provides the wrapper for message receiving/sending. 

To craft and consume the message, you will need the protobuf right?

> `DASH_ENI_TABLE` is added already [eni.proto](https://github.com/sonic-net/sonic-dash-api/blob/master/proto/eni.proto).

I see, got it!

> Swss-comm only provides the wrapper for message receiving/sending.
> To craft and consume the message, you will need the protobuf right?

I may be misunderstanding something, but I don't know where protobuf comes into the picture. When hamgrd wants to update DASH_HA_SET_TABLE: 
- hamgrd calls ZmqProducerStateTable::set [1](https://github.com/sonic-net/sonic-swss-common/blob/c82811f753b4b14c0818eda5d9f3cc924b7e24ae/common/zmqproducerstatetable.cpp#L53-L65)
- set calls ZmqClient::sendMsg [2](https://github.com/sonic-net/sonic-swss-common/blob/c82811f753b4b14c0818eda5d9f3cc924b7e24ae/common/zmqclient.cpp#L123-L133)
- and sendMsg calls serializeBuffer, which runs a custom serialization routine [3](https://github.com/sonic-net/sonic-swss-common/blob/c82811f753b4b14c0818eda5d9f3cc924b7e24ae/common/binaryserializer.h#L36-L71)

I assume the opposite is happening on the other end to convert the message back to a KeyOpFieldValuesTuple object. Is there some point in swss where this message is being converted to a protobuf object?

> > `DASH_ENI_TABLE` is added already [eni.proto](https://github.com/sonic-net/sonic-dash-api/blob/master/proto/eni.proto).
> 
> I see, got it!
> 
> > Swss-comm only provides the wrapper for message receiving/sending.
> > To craft and consume the message, you will need the protobuf right?
> 
> I may be misunderstanding something, but I don't know where protobuf comes into the picture. When hamgrd wants to update DASH_HA_SET_TABLE:
> 
> * hamgrd calls ZmqProducerStateTable::set [1](https://github.com/sonic-net/sonic-swss-common/blob/c82811f753b4b14c0818eda5d9f3cc924b7e24ae/common/zmqproducerstatetable.cpp#L53-L65)
> * set calls ZmqClient::sendMsg [2](https://github.com/sonic-net/sonic-swss-common/blob/c82811f753b4b14c0818eda5d9f3cc924b7e24ae/common/zmqclient.cpp#L123-L133)
> * and sendMsg calls serializeBuffer, which runs a custom serialization routine [3](https://github.com/sonic-net/sonic-swss-common/blob/c82811f753b4b14c0818eda5d9f3cc924b7e24ae/common/binaryserializer.h#L36-L71)
> 
> I assume the opposite is happening on the other end to convert the message back to a KeyOpFieldValuesTuple object. Is there some point in swss where this message is being converted to a protobuf object?

Totally understand your confusion here.

The reason is that, at some point, we decided to refactor the received message into pb objects in swss: https://github.com/sonic-net/sonic-swss/pull/2722 (reasons are mentioned in the PR description). When you call `ZmqProducerStateTable::set`, the field and value need to be `"pb"` and the pb object serialized to string. 

I tried to find you a document for this, but there wasn't any. @Pterosaur - can you confirm above or share a doc?
Ok, yeah I didn't know any of that.
